---
import BaseLayout from '@platform/core/src/layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
import { getSiteConfig, getPersona } from '@platform/core/src/lib/config'
const cfg = getSiteConfig()
const persona = getPersona()
---

<BaseLayout
  title={`How We Research — ${cfg.site.brand_name}`}
  description={`Our research methodology: how ${persona.name_used} evaluates ${cfg.site.niche} products before recommending them.`}
>
  <div class="container" style="padding-top:2rem; padding-bottom:4rem; max-width:720px;">
    <h1>How We Evaluate {cfg.site.niche_label ?? cfg.site.niche} Products</h1>
    <p>Every recommendation on this site is based on verified owner research, manufacturer specifications, and community consensus — not manufacturer claims alone. {persona.name_used}'s familiarity with the category informs how we weigh evidence and what questions matter most.</p>
    <h2>What we evaluate</h2>
    <p>For each product: real-world performance signals from owner communities, specification accuracy versus marketing claims, build quality and durability indicators, value relative to competing options, and whether the product holds up across the use cases our readers actually have.</p>
    <h2>How we source information</h2>
    <p>We draw on verified buyer reports, owner consensus from relevant communities, published specifications, and manufacturer documentation. Where sourcing is particularly relevant to a conclusion, it is noted in the article.</p>
    <h2>What we don't do</h2>
    <p>We don't write "best of" lists based on star ratings alone. We don't accept free products in exchange for coverage. We don't flatten real differences into vague superlatives.</p>
    <h2>Affiliate links</h2>
    <p>Some links on this site are affiliate links. If you buy something through one, we earn a small commission at no extra cost to you. This never influences what we recommend — see our <a href="/affiliate-disclosure/">full affiliate disclosure</a>.</p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
